Andy Lyons/Getty ImagesMontrezl Harrell will likely be a lottery pick if he declares for the 2015 NBA draft. ESPN Insider's Chad Ford and Kevin Pelton return to provide the kind of discussions that are happening in front offices around the NBA -- where scouts and statistical experts are breaking down draft prospects using their "eyes, ears and numbers." For the next several weeks, Ford and Pelton will be breaking down the top returning college prospects in the country by conference. They broke down the Pac-12 on Tuesday. Today they tackle the ACC. Chad Ford: The ACC is full of interesting freshmen like Jahlil Okafor (ranked No. 1 on my Big Board), Justise Winslow (No. 12), Justin Jackson (No. 18) and Tyus Jones (No. 24). But we're tackling returning players in this series. Kevin and I already discussed my top-ranked returning player in the ACC, Louisville's Terry Rozier, last week. Rozier's teammate Montrezl Harrell just happens to be the second-highest-ranked returning ACC player on my board. To read Chad Ford and Kevin Pelton's full story on the best NBA prospects in the ACC, sign up for Insider today. Insider Become an insider and get access to all our articles and tools. Subscribe Sign in View Insider Benefits » Magazine subscribers: activate your Insider account. Recommend0 Tweet0 Email Subscribe Chad FordSenior Writer, NBA Insider Follow Archive Senior NBA Writer for ESPN.com ESPN Insider NBA Draft Analyst since 2002 Writes ESPN's NBA Draft Top 100 and Lottery Mock Draft Kevin Pelton Follow Archive Co-author, Pro Basketball Prospectus series Formerly a consultant with the Indiana Pacers Developed WARP rating and SCHOENE system